    • Method Detail

      • entryaction

        void entryaction(int nodeNr,
                 int level)
          throws IOException
        The action to take on the current node when the TreeWalker enters it. (Before the node's children are processed.)
        Parameters:
        nodeNr - the number of the current node
        level - the level of the node below the node that the TreeWalker started to walk on
        Throws:
        IOException - if the implementation throws one.

      • exitaction

        void exitaction(int nodeNr,
                int level)
         throws IOException
        The action to take on the current node when the TreeWalker exits it. (After the node's children are processed.)
        Parameters:
        nodeNr - the number of the current node
        level - the level of the node below the node that the TreeWalker started to walk on
        Throws:
        IOException - if the implementation throws one.
